I opened a few cans.

175
0:21:15,870 --> 0:21:19,280
是个气候考察\n我曾经打过北极熊
It was a weather expedition.\nAnd I shot a polar bear.

176
0:21:19,450 --> 0:21:21,450
-不会吧\n-好吧 我没打中
-No!\n-Well, I didn't hit it.

177
0:21:21,620 --> 0:21:24,700
为什么开枪打北极熊？\n这事可真恶心
Why shoot a polar bear?\nThat's a lousy thing to do.

178
0:21:24,870 --> 0:21:27,450
因为我发现
Because I found it...

179
0:21:27,620 --> 0:21:31,160
用它的脸 听着-\n在冰激凌机里面
..with its face -Listen to this -\nin the ice-cream mixer.

180
0:21:33,030 --> 0:21:36,370
这段我没法忘记\n因为我们靠冰激凌机过活
I couldn't let that pass\nbecause we lived off ice cream.

181
0:21:40,030 --> 0:21:42,030
你已经语无伦次了 汉伯特
You're out of your gourd, Humpy.

182
0:21:43,660 --> 0:21:46,080
你能不能不要用这个布娃娃来烦人了？
Will you stop fidgeting with the doll?

183
0:21:47,700 --> 0:21:50,410
现在我们都认为洛应该去睡觉了
And now we all think\nthat Lo should go to bed.

184
0:21:50,580 --> 0:21:52,580
洛？
Lo?

185
0:21:52,740 --> 0:21:54,740
你的“我们”是指谁 白脸女人？
What do you mean "we", paleface?

186
0:21:56,040 --> 0:22:00,200
如我所说 我把我的打北极熊的枪
So, as I was saying, there I was\nwith my white polar-bear gun...

187
0:22:02,240 --> 0:22:04,910
来搅拌
-..to blend in.

188
0:22:05,080 --> 0:22:07,080
找我的！
It's for me!

189
0:22:09,410 --> 0:22:10,370
喂？
Hello?

190
0:22:11,200 --> 0:22:16,200
-不 不好意思 她很忙\n-希望你原谅她的没礼貌
-No, I'm sorry. She's busy.\n-I hope you will forgive her bad manners.

191
0:22:16,370 --> 0:22:18,330
-又怎么样？！
-Now what?!

192
0:22:18,500 --> 0:22:21,040
看着 我的独创现代舞
Look! It's my modern dance creation!

193
0:22:25,750 --> 0:22:28,870
多丽丝·海兹 关掉那音乐！
Dolores Haze, turn that music down!

194
0:22:31,500 --> 0:22:35,870
她是个害虫 如果她打扰了你的思考的话直接抽她就行
She is a pest. Just slap her hard\nif she interferes with your meditations.

195
0:22:39,000 --> 0:22:40,410
切！
Psst!

196
0:22:53,080 --> 0:22:54,830
嗯
Hum...

197
0:22:55,000 --> 0:22:59,410
汉 你是不是认为我有一个很野心的梦？
Hum, do you know that I have\none most ambitious dream?

198
0:22:59,580 --> 0:23:01,910
去找一个真正培训过的女仆人
To get a hold of a real trained maid...

199
0:23:02,080 --> 0:23:05,410
就跟那个德国女孩子一样\n跟那个塔波特说的一样
..like that German girl\nthat the Talbots spoke of...

200
0:23:05,580 --> 0:23:07,580
让她住在房子里面
..and have her live in the house.

201
0:23:07,750 --> 0:23:09,750
-没房间了吧\n-噢 亲爱的 亲爱的
-No room.\n-Oh, chéri, chéri.

202
0:23:09,910 --> 0:23:13,950
你低估了我们的那卑微的房子
You underestimate the possibilities\nof our humble household.

203
0:23:14,120 --> 0:23:16,210
我会让她住在洛的房间里
We'd put her in Lo's room.

204
0:23:16,370 --> 0:23:19,910
我本来打算把门开在客人房的
I intended to turn that hole\ninto a guest room anyway.

205
0:23:20,080 --> 0:23:22,080
那么洛睡在哪里？
But where would Lo sleep?

206
0:23:22,250 --> 0:23:25,540
小洛完全不在此计划中
Little Lo does not enter the picture at all.

207
0:23:25,710 --> 0:23:29,660
小洛将会去参加寄宿学校举行的野营活动
Little Lo goes straight from camp\nto a good boarding school...

208
0:23:29,830 --> 0:23:33,790
有严格的纪律\n以及一些合理的宗教培训
..with strict discipline\nand some sound religious training.

209
0:23:36,910 --> 0:23:38,870
我不去！
I won't go!

210
0:23:39,240 --> 0:23:43,330
我要把所有这些名字标签在明天都缝到你的衣服上
I want all of these name tags\nsewn on your clothes by tomorrow.

211
0:23:44,870 --> 0:23:46,870
我不想去
I don't want to go.

212
0:23:47,040 --> 0:23:48,660
我想我不是在征求你的意见
I didn't ask your opinion!

213
0:23:48,830 --> 0:23:51,250
我不想去你不能强迫我
I don't want to go and you can't make me.

214
0:23:51,410 --> 0:23:54,580
听着 我们都认为这是个好主意
Look, we all think it's a good idea.

215
0:23:54,750 --> 0:23:59,540
汉伯特教授认为这是个好主意\n我认为这是个好主意 你必须得去
Professor Humbert thinks it's a good idea,\nI think it's a good idea, and you are going!

216
0:24:03,000 --> 0:24:04,580
两面派！
Double-crosser!

217
0:24:05,250 --> 0:24:06,960
嗷
Ow!

218
0:24:07,920 --> 0:24:12,000
我一个小时之前就让你把箱子塞进车子里了
I asked you to put that suitcase\nin the car an hour ago!

219
0:24:12,210 --> 0:24:15,540
露易丝 非常感谢你帮助这屁孩子
Louise, thank you so much\nfor helping the poor child.

220
0:24:17,960 --> 0:24:22,870
天杀的！多丽丝 我告诉你把野餐篮子放在后座上！
Goddamn it! Dolores, I told you\nto put this lunch basket in the back seat!

221
0:24:23,040 --> 0:24:25,250
为什么老是让我去做什么？
Why always tell me to do everything?

222
0:24:25,420 --> 0:24:27,630
我是唯一的不吃你那一套的
I'm the one that won't be eating it.

223
0:24:27,790 --> 0:24:31,040
露易丝！晚饭吃布鲁塞尔菜芽和面包夹肉
Louise! Brussels sprouts\nand meat loaf for dinner.

224
0:24:31,210 --> 0:24:34,290
-好的 开车小心\n-谢谢 走了
-All right. Drive careful.\n-Thank you. Let's go!

225
0:24:34,460 --> 0:24:36,460
-再见 夫人\n-再见 露易丝
-Bye, my baby.\n-Bye, Louise.

226
0:24:36,630 --> 0:24:39,120
-你真是太好了 我会想你的\n-啊！
-You be good. I'm gonna miss you.\n-Agh!

227
0:24:40,580 --> 0:24:42,580
多丽丝！
Dolores!

228
0:24:42,750 --> 0:24:44,880
快走！
Let's go!

229
0:24:45,040 --> 0:24:46,830
快点！
Speed it up!

230
0:24:47,000 --> 0:24:48,750
快上车！
Get in the car!

231
0:24:53,710 --> 0:24:56,460
又要干吗？这屁孩子！
Now what?! That child!

232
0:25:01,580 --> 0:25:04,250
-露易丝 牛腰肉也行\n-好的
-Louise, maybe tenderloin.\n-That'd be good.

233
0:25:52,290 --> 0:25:54,290
我在等着！
I'm waiting!

234
0:25:55,130 --> 0:25:58,500
有没有跟你说过 \n我已经跟你说过一千次了
If I've told you once,\nI've told you a thousand times...

235
0:25:58,670 --> 0:26:01,090
别让我在车上等你
..not to make me wait in the car.

236
0:26:02,300 --> 0:26:05,550
如果你不是去野营 \n我就把你给撂倒
If you weren't going to camp,\nI would ground you.

237
0:26:29,590 --> 0:26:31,590
汉伯先生！
Mr Humble!

238
0:26:31,750 --> 0:26:34,630
这些该死的楼梯快把我给整死了
These damn stairs\nare gonna be the death of me.

239
0:26:34,800 --> 0:26:36,550
汉伯先生！
Mr Humble!

240
0:26:37,840 --> 0:26:39,420
汉伯先生！
Mr Humble!

241
0:26:39,590 --> 0:26:41,590
汉伯先生？
Mr Humble?

242
0:26:45,630 --> 0:26:47,630
我有东西要给你
I have something for you.

243
0:26:47,800 --> 0:26:49,960
哦 是吧
Oh, yes.

244
0:26:50,130 --> 0:26:53,460
我要走了 很快就回来
I'm leaving, but I'll be back later.

245
0:26:56,760 --> 0:26:59,340
你他娘的还在那里干什么？
What the hell he doin' in there?

246
0:27:03,050 --> 0:27:05,260
这是一个忏悔
This is a confession.

247
0:27:05,420 --> 0:27:07,420
我爱你
I love you.

248
0:27:07,590 --> 0:27:09,920
我是个激情的可爱的女人？
I'm a passionate and lonely woman...

249
0:27:10,090 --> 0:27:12,090
你是我一生所爱
..and you are the love of my life.

250
0:27:12,260 --> 0:27:14,260
现在你知道了
Now you know.

251
0:27:14,420 --> 0:27:16,840
请毁了这封信然后走吧
So please, destroy this letter and go.

252
0:27:17,760 --> 0:27:21,340
我将会在晚餐时回来\n你那时必须走
I shall return by dinner time\nand you must be gone by then.

253
0:27:23,050 --> 0:27:25,590
听着 亲爱的 如果我发现你在家？
You see, chéri, if I found you at home,...

254
0:27:25,760 --> 0:27:29,260
如果你仍然在家那么只代表一件事
..the fact of your remaining\nwould mean only one thing.

255
0:27:29,420 --> 0:27:33,590
你需要我就跟我需要你一样 \n称为一生的伴侣
That you want me as much as I do you,\nas a lifelong mate,...

256
0:27:33,760 --> 0:27:38,670
而且你已经准备将你\n和我的生命永远连在一起
..and that you are ready to link up\nyour life with mine forever and ever...

257
0:27:38,840 --> 0:27:41,670
并且做我女儿的父亲
..and be a father to my little girl.

258
0:27:43,880 --> 0:27:48,550
两周之后 \n我们在一个简单的仪式中结了婚
Two weeks later,\nwe were married in a simple ceremony.

259
0:27:48,720 --> 0:27:52,880
老海兹确保小海兹没有参加
Big Haze made sure little Haze\nwas not in attendance.

260
0:27:58,700 --> 0:28:00,700
嗯 这可真是天降的福气
Mm. This is bliss.

261
0:28:00,590 --> 0:28:03,010
这简直是地上的天堂 不是吗 汉？
This is heaven on earth. Isn't it, Hump?

262
0:28:03,170 --> 0:28:05,170
嗯
Mm.

263
0:28:08,470 --> 0:28:10,970
你在写你的书吗？
Are you working on your book?

264
0:28:11,130 --> 0:28:13,130
是的
Yes.

265
0:28:21,130 --> 0:28:23,470
哦 一个秘密的抽屉 里面是什么？
Oh, a secret drawer. What's in there?

266
0:28:25,300 --> 0:28:27,300
锁起来的情书
Locked-up love letters.

267
0:28:28,800 --> 0:28:30,800
钥匙在哪里？
Where's the key?

268
0:28:31,760 --> 0:28:34,050
藏起来了
Hidden.

269
0:28:34,220 --> 0:28:37,380
"I'm in the Mood for Love"
"I'm in the Mood for Love")

270
0:28:40,800 --> 0:28:07,930
在我们结婚后的头六周
During the six weeks\nwe'd been married,...

271
0:28:44,090 --> 0:28:47,590
我成功地逃脱了大部分的丈夫的职责
..I successfully avoided\nmost of my husbandly duties.

272
0:28:51,050 --> 0:28:55,680
整个七月 我一直给夏洛特各种不同的安眠药 ?
Throughout July, I'd been offering\nCharlotte various sleeping tablets,...

273
0:28:55,840 --> 0:28:58,010
她很开心地吞下它们
..which she gobbled down happily.

274
0:28:58,180 --> 0:29:00,180
她吃药很强
She was a great taker of pills.

275
0:29:02,680 --> 0:29:06,550
♪ I'm in the mood for love ♪

276
0:29:07,470 --> 0:29:11,090
♪ Simply because you're near me ♪

277
0:29:11,890 --> 0:29:15,510
♪ Funny, but when you're near me ♪

278
0:29:16,180 --> 0:29:19,800
♪ I'm in the mood for love ♪

279
0:29:20,970 --> 0:29:24,550
♪ Heaven is in your eyes ♪

280
0:29:24,720 --> 0:29:28,300
♪ Bright as the stars we're under ♪

281
0:29:29,700 --> 0:29:32,930
♪ Oh, is it any wonder... ♪

282
0:29:33,100 --> 0:29:36,800
我尝试的最后一种药把她放倒了四个小时
The last dose I had tried\nhad knocked her out for four hours.

283
0:29:36,970 --> 0:29:41,010
但是并不足够能保证我晚上不被打扰
But that was not enough\nto guarantee me an undisturbed night.

284
0:29:43,970 --> 0:29:45,970
汉
Hum...

285
0:29:46,800 --> 0:29:48,800
你逃不出我的手掌心！
At last!

286
0:29:50,890 --> 0:29:52,260
嗯
Mm.

287
0:29:54,390 --> 0:29:56,390
我想这个东西不太管用
I think I must be immune.

288
0:29:59,510 --> 0:30:02,600
嗯…你会给我什么东西 如果你是想
Wh... What would you give me\nif you wanted to uh...

289
0:30:02,760 --> 0:30:04,510
放倒
..to knock out...

290
0:30:04,680 --> 0:30:06,390
比如一头母牛？
..say, a cow?

291
0:30:08,010 --> 0:30:11,140
七八个小时就可以
J-Just for... seven or eight hours.

292
0:30:11,310 --> 0:30:12,890
确保
So that...

293
0:30:14,720 --> 0:30:18,050
这头母牛睡得很死？
..you know, the cow... would stay asleep?

294
0:30:20,560 --> 0:30:24,060
即使你在旁边乱动并转身？
Even if you were\ntossing and turning next to it.

295
0:30:25,100 --> 0:30:26,720
那么
Well...

296
0:30:26,890 --> 0:30:28,260
你为什么不…
Why don't you...

297
0:30:28,700 --> 0:30:30,010
试试这个？
..try these?

298
0:30:30,180 --> 0:30:31,760
最新的药
They're new.

299
0:30:33,310 --> 0:30:35,760
我老婆吃了这药
My wife takes them and...

300
0:30:35,930 --> 0:30:39,700
我整夜都没听到她吭一声
..I don't hear a peep out of her\nall night long.

301
0:30:40,760 --> 0:30:42,760
听起来就是我想要的东西
Sounds like just the thing.

302
0:30:54,850 --> 0:30:56,850
我回家了！
I'm home!

303
0:30:59,560 --> 0:31:01,140
有人吗？
Hello?

304
0:31:06,350 --> 0:31:07,930
有人吗？
Hello?

305
0:31:09,270 --> 0:31:10,850
有人吗？
Hello?

306
0:31:21,060 --> 0:31:23,060
海兹老女人？
"The Haze woman."

307
0:31:24,640 --> 0:31:26,640
肥母牛？
"The fat cow"?

308
0:31:29,060 --> 0:31:31,060
讨人厌的大咪咪？
"The obnoxious mamma"?

309
0:31:34,640 --> 0:31:39,350
那么 这个又老又蠢的海兹老女人不会再受你的骗了
Well, the "old stupid Haze woman"\nis no longer your dupe.

310
0:31:39,520 --> 0:31:41,890
夏洛特
Charlotte!

311
0:31:44,100 --> 0:31:46,560
你是个怪物
You're a monster.

312
0:31:46,730 --> 0:31:50,180
-你是个卑鄙的 罪恶的禽兽
-You're a despicable, criminal monster.

313
0:31:50,350 --> 0:31:53,020
-听我说\n-如果你靠近我我会尖叫！
-Now...\n-If you come near me I'll scream!

314
0:31:53,180 --> 0:31:55,270
-听我解释\n-离我远点！
-Let me just...\n-Get away from me!

315
0:31:55,700 --> 0:31:57,560
我今晚就走
I'm leaving tonight.

316
0:31:57,730 --> 0:32:00,060
你可以得到这个房子 我不在乎
You can keep this house. I don't care.

317
0:32:01,520 --> 0:32:06,640
但是你永远不会再看到那个可怜的毛孩子
But you will never see\nthat miserable brat ever again.

318
0:32:09,390 --> 0:32:12,140
现在快滚出我的视线！
Now get out of my sight!

319
0:32:29,980 --> 0:32:31,980
夏洛特 你不能…
Charlotte, you mustn't...

320
0:32:32,140 --> 0:32:34,140
你不能就这样毁了我们的生活
You mustn't ruin our lives.

321
0:32:36,560 --> 0:32:38,560
那只是…
That's...

322
0:32:40,730 --> 0:32:44,140
那只是 那只是我所写的小说的
That's just... That's just a fragment of...

323
0:32:44,310 --> 0:32:45,440
一个片段
..a novel I'm writing.

324
0:32:47,350 --> 0:32:49,690
我只是用了你的名字
I used your name on those...

325
0:32:49,850 --> 0:32:52,100
仅仅图方便
..just for... convenience.

326
0:32:54,520 --> 0:32:56,520
我去弄点喝的
I'll get us a drink.

327
0:33:12,730 --> 0:33:15,940
一点带冰的饮料能让我们头脑清醒
A nice stiff drink\nwill clear both our heads.

328
0:33:21,440 --> 0:33:23,850
夏洛特 我给我们做了点加冰的饮料
Charlotte, I made us a nice stiff drink!

329
0:33:26,100 --> 0:33:28,100
喂？
Yes?

330
0:33:29,600 --> 0:33:31,600
但那真是荒谬
But that's ridiculous.

331
0:33:32,520 --> 0:33:37,350
电话里那个男人说你死了 夏洛特
There's this man on the phone\nsaying you've been killed, Charlotte.

332
0:33:38,230 --> 0:33:39,610
夏洛特？
Charlotte?

333
0:34:20,570 --> 0:34:22,900
对不起
I'm... I'm sorry.

334
0:34:28,270 --> 0:34:30,360
请往后站
Stand back, please.

335
0:34:31,400 --> 0:34:33,520
我妻子在哪里？
Where's my wife?

336
0:34:34,360 --> 0:34:37,770
-你是汉伯特先生吗？\n-我是
-Are you Mr Humbert?\n-I am.

337
0:34:39,810 --> 0:34:41,810
她直接跑向我
She ran right in front of me.

338
0:34:41,980 --> 0:34:44,150
我 我甚至没有看到她
I... I didn't even see her.

339
0:34:48,360 --> 0:34:50,190
先生？
Sir?

340
0:34:54,570 --> 0:34:56,570
对不起 先生
I'm sorry, sir.

341
0:34:56,730 --> 0:34:58,690
这是汉伯特夫人吗？
Is this Mrs Humbert?

342
0:35:02,110 --> 0:35:03,650
先生
Sir,...\nSir,...

343
0:35:03,820 --> 0:35:05,860
这是汉伯特夫人吗？
..is this Mrs Humbert?

344
0:35:08,940 --> 0:35:10,900
噢 老天爷
Oh, God...

345
0:35:12,110 --> 0:35:15,360
噢 老天爷 噢 老天爷！
Oh, God... Oh, God!

346
0:35:27,690 --> 0:35:30,070
她那时正走向邮箱
She was walking to the mailbox.

347
0:35:31,280 --> 0:35:33,530
她准备寄掉这些信
She was going to mail these letters.

348
0:35:35,280 --> 0:35:36,860
对不起
I'm sorry.

349
0:35:37,980 --> 0:35:40,030
谢谢
Thank you.

350
0:35:44,690 --> 0:35:46,110
我要回去 躺一会 警官
I'll go and... Lie down, officer.

351
0:35:46,320 --> 0:35:49,400
-可以吗？\n-你直接走吧 先生
-Will that be all right?\n-You go right ahead, sir.

352
0:35:49,570 --> 0:35:52,530
我只是进房间 如果你
I'll just be across in the house if you...

353
0:37:22,360 --> 0:37:24,700
请问这是Enchanted Hunter宾馆吗？
Is that the Enchanted Hunters Hotel?

354
0:37:24,860 --> 0:37:26,860
是的 这是汉伯特先生
Yes. This is Mr Humbert.

355
0:37:27,030 --> 0:37:28,990
明天晚上
Tomorrow night.

356
0:37:29,160 --> 0:37:31,160
只一夜
Just the one night, please.

357
0:37:33,030 --> 0:37:35,030
是的 一个两张床的标准间
Yes, a room with twin beds.

358
0:37:35,200 --> 0:37:38,740
两个人 实际上是一个半人
For two.\nWell, one and a half people, really.

359
0:37:38,910 --> 0:37:40,780
仅仅是我和我的
It's just for me and my...

360
0:37:40,950 --> 0:37:44,700
我的个子不高的 我的小女儿
..my short... my small daughter.

361
0:38:22,870 --> 0:38:24,780
她随时都可能到
She should be here any minute.

362
0:38:25,280 --> 0:38:28,030
我让查理去谷仓那边找她了
I sent Charlie for her over at the barn.

363
0:38:30,070 --> 0:38:32,530
-谁是查理？\n-快点 快点
-Who's Charlie?\n-Come on, come on.

364
0:38:34,570 --> 0:38:38,370
看着我们的这些孩子们交朋友真让人开心
It's such a pleasure to watch\nour young people make friends.

365
0:38:38,530 --> 0:38:41,240
-嗯 谁是查理？\n-她来了
-So uh... who is this Charlie?\n-Here she is.

366
0:38:54,870 --> 0:38:56,700
嗨 老爹
Hi, Dad!

367
0:38:56,870 --> 0:39:00,200
♪ Hum and Mum, Mum and Hum ♪

368
0:39:00,370 --> 0:39:04,370
♪ Hum and Mum, Mum and Hum ♪

369
0:39:04,530 --> 0:39:06,950
♪ Hum and Mum, Mum and Hum... ♪

370
0:39:07,120 --> 0:39:10,780
-妈妈怎么样了？\n-嗯 医生说还不确定
-How's Mum?\n-Well... The doctors aren't quite sure.

371
0:39:10,950 --> 0:39:13,200
腹部有问题
It's something abdominal.

372
0:39:15,530 --> 0:39:17,030
讨人厌？
Abominable?

373
0:39:17,700 --> 0:39:19,200
腹部问题
Abdominal.

374
0:39:24,990 --> 0:39:28,490
她在列平威尔的一家特殊的医院里
She's in a special hospital\nover in Lepingville.

375
0:39:28,660 --> 0:39:31,330
所以 我想我们应该 我们应该
So... I thought we'd... we'd...

376
0:39:31,490 --> 0:39:33,870
去布来士兰
..go over to Briceland,...

377
0:39:34,040 --> 0:39:37,790
待一夜然后去那个医院
..spend the night there and...\nvisit the hospital tomorrow.

378
0:39:37,950 --> 0:39:39,790
或者过一天去
Or the next day.

379
0:39:45,040 --> 0:39:47,200
野营玩得开心吗？
So, did you have a good time at camp?

380
0:39:47,370 --> 0:39:49,160
嗯 嗯
Mm-hm.

381
0:39:50,490 --> 0:39:52,490
你知道吗？我想你
You know, I missed you.

382
0:39:52,660 --> 0:39:54,660
我很想你
I missed you a lot.

383
0:39:54,830 --> 0:39:57,410
可我不想你
Well, I didn't miss you.

384
0:39:57,580 --> 0:40:00,750
实际上 我令人作呕地欺骗了你
In fact, I've been\nrevoltingly unfaithful to you.

385
0:40:00,910 --> 0:40:04,410
但又怎样呢？反正你根本一点点都不在乎我
But so what? Cos you don't care\nabout me any more anyway.

386
0:40:04,580 --> 0:40:07,580
为什么你认为我不在乎你？
Why do you think I don't care about you?

387
0:40:07,750 --> 0:40:10,790
你还没有亲我呢？不是吗？
Well, you haven't\nkissed me yet, have you?

388
0:40:39,120 --> 0:40:40,580
噢！
Oh!

389
0:40:41,790 --> 0:40:45,330
-嗯 不好意思 警官\n-有没有看见一辆蓝色的汽车 跟你的差不多？
-Uh, I'm sorry, officer.\n-See a blue sedan, same make as yours?

390
0:40:45,500 --> 0:40:50,450
-他们或许在那个路口超过去了\n-蓝色轿车？没有 我想没有
-They might have passed you at the turn.\n-Blue sedan? No, I don't think... agh!

391
0:40:50,620 --> 0:40:54,450
-我们没有看见蓝色轿车\n-没有 我认为没有
-We didn't see a blue sedan.\n-No, I don't think we did.

392
0:40:54,620 --> 0:40:58,040
你确定是蓝色的？\n我看见一个更像是紫色的
Are you sure it was blue?\nI saw one that was more purple.

393
0:40:58,210 --> 0:41:00,330
或者更像红色
Or maybe it was more red.

394
0:41:00,500 --> 0:41:02,580
好的 谢谢
All right, OK. Thank you.

395
0:41:03,460 --> 0:41:06,210
谢谢
-Thank you!

396
0:41:06,370 --> 0:41:08,710
不要开枪 不要开枪
Don't shoot, don't shoot!

397
0:41:24,410 --> 0:41:26,410
哇！看起来真不错！
Wow! Looks swank!

398
0:41:36,250 --> 0:41:38,790
♪ No, I will never tell lies ♪

399
0:41:38,960 --> 0:41:41,910
♪ But still I'm called Buttercup... ♪

400
0:41:42,080 --> 0:41:45,960
晚上好 我以汉伯特的名字预定了一个房间
Good evening. I have a reservation\nin the name of Humbert.

401
0:41:46,120 --> 0:41:48,120
两张房的标间
Twin-bedded room.

402
0:41:48,290 --> 0:41:50,960
昨晚打过电话的
I called last night.

403
0:41:51,120 --> 0:41:53,790
-两个人\n-哦！
-Two people.\n-Oh!

404
0:41:53,920 --> 0:41:55,710
对不起 汉八哥先生
I'm sorry, Mr Humbug.

405
0:41:55,870 --> 0:42:01,210
这个房间我给你留到了六点半 但是后来没接到你的电话
I held the room with the twin beds for you\ntill 6.30, but I didn't hear from you.

406
0:42:01,330 --> 0:42:06,830
我们保留到了六点半 有花园景色以及基督公约
We hold till 6.30. And with the flower\nshow and Glory of Christ convention...

407
0:42:07,000 --> 0:42:09,250
我名字不是汉八哥 是赫伯特
My name is not Humbug. It's Herbert.

408
0:42:09,830 --> 0:42:11,330
汉伯特
Humbert.

409
0:42:12,710 --> 0:42:16,960
那么随便找个房间吧 找个吊床给我的女儿 她很累了
Just put us in any room. Put a cot in\nfor my daughter. She's very tired.

410
0:42:19,380 --> 0:42:22,790
或许 我可以让你住342房间 有两张床
Perhaps I could put you in room 342.\nIt has a double bed.

411
0:42:22,960 --> 0:42:26,420
我希望可以\n我妻子可能待会就到
I expect we'll manage.\nMy wife may be turning up later.

412
0:42:30,290 --> 0:42:32,290
请在这里签名 先生
Please sign here, mister.

413
0:42:38,630 --> 0:42:40,790
是只漂亮的狗 对吗？
It's a nice dog, huh?

414
0:42:40,960 --> 0:42:42,960
我喜欢狗
I love dogs.

415
0:42:45,000 --> 0:42:47,000
这是我的狗
Well, that's my dog.

416
0:42:47,170 --> 0:42:48,880
它喜欢你
He likes you.

417
0:42:49,040 --> 0:42:51,590
它不是喜欢每个人的
Doesn't like everybody.

418
0:42:53,830 --> 0:42:55,840
它喜欢什么样的？
Who does he like?

419
0:42:57,000 --> 0:42:59,170
他能闻出来甜美的人
He can smell when people are sweet.

420
0:43:00,700 --> 0:43:01,590
他喜欢甜美的人
He likes sweet people.

421
0:43:02,250 --> 0:43:04,550
年轻的漂亮的人
Nice young people.

422
0:43:04,560 --> 0:43:06,520
比如你
Like you.

423
0:43:15,840 --> 0:43:17,840
到了
Here we are.

424
0:43:38,050 --> 0:43:40,050
谢谢
Thanks very much.

425
0:43:42,300 --> 0:43:45,170
等一下 你意思是我们睡在一个房间里？
Wait a sec. You mean\nwe're sleeping in one room?

426
0:43:47,050 --> 0:43:49,170
一张床上？
With one bed?

427
0:43:49,340 --> 0:43:51,670
我让他们送一张吊床过来
I've asked them to send up a cot,...

428
0:43:51,840 --> 0:43:53,840
给我用 如果你愿意的话
..which I'll use, if you like.

429
0:43:58,130 --> 0:43:59,880
你简直是疯了
You're crazy.

430
0:44:00,050 --> 0:44:02,590
为什么 亲爱的？
Why, my darling?

431
0:44:02,750 --> 0:44:04,750
因为 亲爱的
Because, my darling,...

432
0:44:04,920 --> 0:44:09,460
当我亲爱的妈妈发现了 她会和你离婚而且勒死我
..when my darling mother finds out,\nshe'll divorce you and strangle me.

433
0:44:09,630 --> 0:44:11,130
洛
Lo,...

434
0:44:11,300 --> 0:44:13,300
听着
..listen to me a moment.

435
0:44:13,460 --> 0:44:16,420
从一切实际的意图来说 我是你老爹
For all practical purposes,\nI am your father,...

436
0:44:16,590 --> 0:44:19,010
并对你的幸福负责
..and I'm responsible for your welfare.

437
0:44:19,170 --> 0:44:21,710
现在 我们并不富有
Now, we're not rich.

438
0:44:21,880 --> 0:44:26,510
所以 我们旅行的时候我们肯定会\n我的意思是 呆在一起
So when we travel, we-we're sure to be...\nI mean, we'll be thrown together.

439
0:44:28,880 --> 0:44:30,130
有时
Sometimes.

440
0:44:30,300 --> 0:44:33,260
两个人呆在一个宾馆房间里
Two people sharing\nthe same hotel room...

441
0:44:33,420 --> 0:44:36,340
应该 成为一个
..are bound to... enter into a...

442
0:44:36,510 --> 0:44:38,670
我该怎么说？成为
How can I put it? Into a kind of um...

443
0:44:38,920 --> 0:44:40,920
那个词是“乱伦”
The word is "incest".

444
0:44:56,130 --> 0:44:58,800
我感到我们成年了
I feel like we're grown-ups.

445
0:44:58,920 --> 0:45:00,920
我也是
Me too.

446
0:45:01,090 --> 0:45:03,470
我们将会去我们想去的任何地方 对吗？
We get to do whatever we want, right?

447
0:45:03,630 --> 0:45:05,590
想去的任何地方
Whatever we want.

448
0:45:05,760 --> 0:45:07,340
那么好吧
Well, now.

449
0:45:07,510 --> 0:45:09,300
谁叫的派？
Who had the pie?

450
0:45:10,800 --> 0:45:12,340
我
Me.

451
0:45:16,170 --> 0:45:19,550
你在想什么？这是我的吗？
Whaddaya think? Are they me?

452
0:45:24,920 --> 0:45:26,920
-别看\n-为什么？
-Don't look now.\n-Why?

453
0:45:27,090 --> 0:45:29,090
那个坐在角落的家伙
The guy over in the corner.

454
0:45:29,920 --> 0:45:32,340
别看！ 他正盯着我们
Don't look! He was staring at us.

455
0:45:32,510 --> 0:45:35,880
你不觉得那个家伙看起来像奎尔第吗？
Don't you think that guy\nlooks exactly like Quilty?

456
0:45:36,050 --> 0:45:38,510
什么 那个牙医？
What, the dentist?

457
0:45:38,670 --> 0:45:41,260
当然不是 他兄弟
Of course not. His brother.

458
0:45:41,700 --> 0:45:44,510
作家奎尔第\n他是剧作家
The writer Quilty.\nYou know, he writes the plays.

459
0:45:44,680 --> 0:45:47,930
那个抽烟的家伙 他在广告中抽Dromes的烟
The smoking guy.\nHe smokes the Dromes in the ad.

460
0:45:48,090 --> 0:45:50,260
我们在大厅看到过他和他的狗
We saw him in the lobby with his dog.

461
0:46:05,720 --> 0:46:08,260
如果我告诉你我在野营的时候多么不齿
If I tell you how naughty I was at camp,...

462
0:46:10,050 --> 0:46:12,050
你保证不会疯掉？
..you promise you won't be mad?

463
0:46:13,050 --> 0:46:15,050
待会告诉我
Tell me later.

464
0:46:18,840 --> 0:46:20,840
我让你上床睡觉
I want you to go to bed.

465
0:46:22,510 --> 0:46:24,640
你脱衣服的时候我会去楼下
I'll go downstairs while you...

466
0:46:25,970 --> 0:46:28,510
当我回来时 我希望你已经睡着
When I come up, I want you to be asleep.

467
0:46:29,380 --> 0:46:30,890
好吗？
All right?

468
0:46:42,590 --> 0:46:44,680
我真是个恶心的女孩子
I've been such a disgusting girl.

469
0:46:45,840 --> 0:46:47,840
让我告诉你吧
Just let me tell you.

470
0:46:48,010 --> 0:46:50,010
明天再说
Tell me tomorrow.

471
0:46:51,220 --> 0:46:53,220
我现在就走 明白？
I'm going to go now. All right?

472
0:46:54,840 --> 0:46:56,840
晚安 老爹
Good night, Dad.

473
0:47:08,680 --> 0:47:10,680
晚安
Night-night.

474
0:47:21,470 --> 0:47:23,470
陪审团的女士们
Gentlewomen of the jury,...

475
0:47:25,220 --> 0:47:28,100
如果我的快乐可以言表
..if my happiness could have talked,...

476
0:47:28,260 --> 0:47:32,260
那么那个宾馆将会充满震耳欲聋的呐喊
..it would have filled that hotel\nwith a deafening roar.

477
0:47:33,140 --> 0:47:35,140
我只是后悔
My only regret...

478
0:47:35,300 --> 0:47:39,550
没有立即把342房间的钥匙保存在办公室里
..is that I did not immediately deposit\nkey number 342 at the office...

479
0:47:39,720 --> 0:47:44,350
然后离开那个小镇 那个国家 那个星球 就在那天晚上
..and leave the town, the country,\nthe planet, that very night.

480
0:47:44,510 --> 0:47:50,600
上帝知道一切 上帝看到一切 上帝宽恕一切
The Lord knows all,\nthe Lord sees all, the Lord forgives all.

481
0:48:11,390 --> 0:48:13,810
你在哪里得到的这个魔女？
Where the devil did you get her?

482
0:48:21,060 --> 0:48:24,720
-不好意思？\n-我说马上就会下雨
-I beg your pardon?\n-I said the weather's getting better.

483
0:48:30,970 --> 0:48:32,970
看起来是的
It seems so.

484
0:48:33,140 --> 0:48:35,140
这个女孩子是谁？
Who's the lassie?

485
0:48:39,060 --> 0:48:41,060
嗯
Um...

486
0:48:42,930 --> 0:48:44,930
这是我女儿
It's my daughter.

487
0:48:45,100 --> 0:48:47,890
你撒谎 她不是
You lie. She's not.

488
0:48:49,310 --> 0:48:50,270
什么？
What?

489
0:48:51,680 --> 0:48:53,680
我说七月份很热 （谐音）
I said July was hot.

490
0:48:56,180 --> 0:48:58,680
她妈妈在哪里？
Where's her mother?

491
0:48:59,810 --> 0:49:01,810
去世了
Dead.

492
0:49:01,970 --> 0:49:03,930
噢 抱歉
Oh. Sorry.

493
0:49:04,100 --> 0:49:06,640
你们明天中午和我共进午餐怎么样？
Why don't you two\nlunch with me tomorrow?

494
0:49:06,810 --> 0:49:09,890
那群牧师很快就要走了
That clerical crowd will be gone soon.

495
0:49:10,560 --> 0:49:12,560
嗯
Um...

496
0:49:13,020 --> 0:49:15,020
我们也很快就走的 谢谢
We'll be gone too, thanks.

497
0:49:15,180 --> 0:49:16,680
晚安
Good night.

498
0:49:16,850 --> 0:49:19,890
抱歉 我喝醉了 晚安
Sorry. I'm very drunk. Good night.

499
0:49:23,730 --> 0:49:26,890
你孩子需要好好睡一觉
That child of yours needs a lot of sleep.

500
0:49:27,060 --> 0:49:29,770
波斯人说“睡眠是一朵玫瑰”
"Sleep is a rose" the Persians say.

501
0:49:32,270 --> 0:49:34,270
抽烟吗？
Smoke?

502
0:49:34,700 --> 0:49:36,640
现在不抽 谢谢
Not just now, thanks.

503
0:49:42,310 --> 0:49:44,770
晚安
Good night.

504
0:49:45,600 --> 0:49:47,600
好好享受
Enjoy.

505
0:51:47,480 --> 0:51:51,190
和查理一起回船上来 你们不必这样
Get back in the boat with Charlie.\nYou don't have to do that.

506
0:51:54,310 --> 0:51:56,520
回船上来
Back in the boat.

507
0:52:14,440 --> 0:52:16,440
我渴了
I'm thirsty.

508
0:52:21,940 --> 0:52:23,940
我给你倒点东西喝
I'll bring you something.

509
0:54:59,860 --> 0:55:03,070
你 你和查理玩那个了？野营的时候？
You... You played that with Charlie?\nAt camp?

510
0:55:03,240 --> 0:55:07,360
别告诉你小时侯从来没有尝试过
Don't tell me you never tried it\nwhen you were a kid.

511
0:55:09,610 --> 0:55:11,820
从来没有
Never.

512
0:55:14,110 --> 0:55:16,990
我想我应该给你看一切
I guess I'm gonna have to\nshow you everything.

513
0:55:41,570 --> 0:55:43,570
陪审团的女士们
Gentlewomen of the jury,...

514
0:55:43,740 --> 0:55:45,740
我甚至不是她的第一个爱人
..I was not even her first lover.

515
0:55:59,030 --> 0:56:01,030
你在看什么？
What are you reading?

516
0:56:01,200 --> 0:56:03,070
没什么
Nothing.

517
0:56:05,410 --> 0:56:07,530
什么事？
What's the matter?

518
0:56:09,660 --> 0:56:11,240
没什么
Nothing.

519
0:56:13,240 --> 0:56:15,240
洛
Lo...

520
0:56:17,490 --> 0:56:20,950
你知道你的那个朋友\n-查理-野营的那个
You know that friend of yours\n-Charlie -at camp?

521
0:56:22,490 --> 0:56:24,490
他是第一个？
Was he the first one?

522
0:56:24,660 --> 0:56:27,200
我们能不能不要谈这个？
Can we please get off the subject?

523
0:56:35,740 --> 0:56:37,990
我感到越来越不爽
I felt more and more uncomfortable.

524
0:56:39,950 --> 0:56:42,910
那种感觉是那么的特别
It was something quite special,\nthat feeling.

525
0:56:43,280 --> 0:56:45,830
一种残酷的 可拍的压抑
An oppressive, hideous constraint,...

526
0:56:45,990 --> 0:56:50,580
就像坐在刚刚杀死的人的鬼魂旁边
..as if I were sitting with the small ghost\nof somebody I had just killed.

527
0:56:53,910 --> 0:56:55,280
耶稣基督
Jesus!

528
0:56:55,450 --> 0:56:56,950
什么？
What?

529
0:56:57,120 --> 0:56:59,370
我们能在加油站边停一停吗？
Can we stop at a gas station?

530
0:56:59,530 --> 0:57:01,950
只要你愿意 去哪儿都行
We can go anywhere you like.

531
0:57:02,120 --> 0:57:04,120
那么好吧 我需要去加油站
Well, I need a gas station.

532
0:57:04,290 --> 0:57:06,080
我里面伤到了
I hurt inside.

